“Today, the situation on the ground has become more stable and secure thanks to successes in the fight against terrorism,” he said.
The Government continues to rebuild the areas destroyed by terrorists so that people can live there in peace.
All conditions are now in place for the voluntary return of refugees to a country they have been forced to leave because of terrorist attacks and unilateral economic measures that have affected their daily lives.
